`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:'IIT Bombays summer internship intake is one of the most sought-after on the Indian academic calendar because of its deep research culture, industry-facing labs in Powai, and a proven pipeline to graduate study and pre-placement interviews. This guide compiles what candidates need to act early: where the 2026 intake is likely to open, how selections typically run, and how to avoid the most common rejections. Any timelines or stipend figures marked as "Expected / Indicative" mirror previous cycles and may shift once official announcements landtreat them as planning guardrails, not certainties.'}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"About the Institute"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"IIT Bombay is consistently ranked among Indias top engineering schools and is known for high-output labs in AI/ML, sustainable energy, advanced materials, aerospace systems, and urban tech. Its location inside Mumbais startup and financial hub attracts sponsored projects and joint R&D with industry, giving interns hands-on exposure instead of shadow work. For breadth across IITs, see the IIT internships hub for context-rich comparisons."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Overview of Summer Internship Programme 2026"}),`
