`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Competitive differentiators: a coherent theme across 23 projects, reproducible results (plots + code), and concise abstracts in your CV. Listing MOOCs without applied work rarely moves the needle."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Who Should Apply"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Apply if you can show alignment to a specific lab in one paragraph: a recent project or artifact, a clear deliverable for 68 weeks, and proof you work independently (clean repos, experiment logs, or hardware evidence). Hardware and systems labs value schematics, measurement logs, or CAD/BOM notes; AI/data labs prefer baselines, error analysis, and reproducibility; design/policy labs appreciate user research or field insights."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Signals that help: quantified outcomes (e.g., latency reductions, accuracy deltas, energy measurements), tidy repos with READMEs, and short Loom or YouTube clips for hardware or UX demos. If you lack prior research, a crisp replication of a lab paper with your own ablation is a strong opener."}),`
